@startuml C4_Pattern_Saga
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Saga/Compensation Pattern

Boundary(forward_path, "Forward Path (Happy Path)") {
    Component(step1, "Step 1: Order", "Task", "Create order")
    Component(step2, "Step 2: Reserve", "Task", "Reserve inventory")
    Component(step3, "Step 3: Charge", "Task", "Charge payment")
    Component(step4, "Step 4: Ship", "Task", "Ship product")
}

Boundary(compensation_path, "Compensation Path (Rollback)") {
    Component(comp1, "Comp 1: Cancel Order", "Task", "Undo order")
    Component(comp2, "Comp 2: Release Inventory", "Task", "Undo reserve")
    Component(comp3, "Comp 3: Refund", "Task", "Undo charge")
}

Boundary(saga_coordinator, "Saga Coordinator") {
    Component(transaction_log, "TransactionLog", "Record", "Track steps")
    Component(rollback_trigger, "RollbackTrigger", "Logic", "On failure")
    Component(idempotency_check, "IdempotencyChecker", "Safety", "Prevent duplicates")
}

step1 --> step2: Success
step2 --> step3: Success
step3 --> step4: Success

step3 --> rollback_trigger: If charge fails
rollback_trigger --> comp3: Reverse charge
comp3 --> comp2: Reverse inventory
comp2 --> comp1: Reverse order

transaction_log --> idempotency_check: Validates
idempotency_check --> step1: Allows only once

Note as N1
Saga Pattern: Long-running transaction
Forward: Step 1 → 2 → 3 → 4
If Step 3 fails:
- Compensate 3 (refund)
- Compensate 2 (release inventory)
- Compensate 1 (cancel order)
Idempotency: Each step safe to repeat
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
